h1. init

h2. Purpose

The @init@ command initialises the appropriate directory structure for a Grails application and sets some common variables for use by the calling script. It is typically used as an include.

h2. Examples

Command line:

{code}
grails init
{code}

or as an include:

{code:java}
includeTargets << grailsScript("_GrailsInit")
{code}
